File: Kiernan Forbes, known as AKA, performs at the 22nd annual South African Music Awards in Durban on June 4, 2016. AFP/Rajesh Jantilal JOHANNESBURG - Kiernan 'AKA' Forbes latest album will drop next week. His family has decided to go ahead with the release of 'Mass Country' as planned. WATCH: AKA's family briefs media following his death AKA first announced the album in January via his social media accounts. His collaborators say he worked extremely hard over the last two years to produce it. READ: AKA to be laid to rest on Saturday The Forbes family says they are honouring his legacy by choosing to continue with the release. AKA was gunned down in Durban last Friday while leaving a restaurant on Florida Road. His death rocked the music fraternity and the country.